Breakfast:
- "Veggie and cheese omelette"

  Ingredients:
  2 tablespoons butter, divided
  1 small onion, chopped
  1 green bell pepper, chopped
  ¾ teaspoon salt, divided
  4 large eggs
  2 tablespoons milk
  ⅛ teaspoon freshly ground black pepper
  2 ounces shredded Swiss cheese

  Directions:
  1. In a bowl, beat 4 eggs with 2 tablespoons of milk, 1/2 teaspoon salt, and pepper.
  2. Melt another tablespoon of butter in the skillet, pour in the egg mixture, and let it set.
  3. Sprinkle 1/4 cup shredded cheese over the eggs, then spoon the vegetable mixture over half.
  4. Gently fold the omelet and cook until the cheese melts.
  5. Slide onto a plate, cut in half, and serve.

- "Protein Pancakes"

  Ingredients: 
  1 banana
  75g oats
  3 large eggs
  2 tbsp milk 
  1 tbsp baking powder
  2 tbsp protein powder 
  nut butter, maple syrup, and berries or sliced banana to serve

  Directions:
  1. Blend 1 banana, 1/2 cup oats, 2 eggs, 1/4 cup milk, 1 tsp baking powder, 1/2 tsp cinnamon, and 1 scoop protein powder until smooth.
  2. Heat oil in a pan.
  3. Pour batter into rounds, cooking for 1-2 mins until bubbles form.
  4. Flip and cook for another minute.
  5. Serve with nut butter, maple syrup, and fruits.

- "Chia Seed Pudding:"

  Ingredients: 
  1/2 cup unsweetened almond milk
  2 tablespoons chia seeds
  2 teaspoons pure maple syrup
  1 teaspoon vanilla extract
  1/2 cup fruit, such as sliced strawberries, blueberries or raspberries 
  1 tablespoon nuts, such as sliced almonds, chopped pistachios or pecans

  Directions:
  1. In a small bowl, stir together 1 cup almond milk, 3 tablespoons chia seeds, 1 tablespoon maple syrup, 1 teaspoon vanilla extract
  2. Cover and refrigerate for at least 8 hours or up to 3 days.
  3. When ready to serve, top with your favorite fruits and nuts. 

Lunch: 
- "Chicken & tzatziki wraps"

  Ingredients: 
  1 cucumber, three-quarters deseeded and coarsely grated, the rest halved and sliced
  250g Greek yogurt
  500g chicken breast, thinly sliced
  2tbsp olive oil
  4 wholemeal wraps
  4 large ripe tomatoes, thinly sliced

  Directions:
  1. Combine 1 grated cucumber and 1 cup yogurt for tzatziki, season.
  2. Season chicken with salt and pepper, rub with 1 tbsp olive oil.
  3. Cook chicken in 1 tbsp olive oil in a pan for 8-10 mins until golden brown.
  4. Spread 2 tbsp tzatziki on each wrap.
  5. Add chicken, tomatoes,sliced cucumber, and season with pepper
  6. Fold sides over filling, roll up tightly, and serve.

- "Pesto spinach penne"

  Ingredients: 
  400g wholemeal penne
  5 tbsp vegetarian basil pesto
  500g baby spinach, roughly chopped
  220g cherry tomatoes, halved

  Directions:
  1. Cook the penne following pack instructions. 
  2. Heat 4 tbsp of the pesto in a non-stick pan over medium-low heat. 
  3. Add the spinach and 2 tbsp water, then cover to wilt.
  4. Drain the pasta and toss it with the spinach, the rest of the pesto, and the tomatoes. 
  5. Serve half. Cool and chill the rest. Will keep chilled for three days. 
  6. Reheat with a splash of water.

- "Veggie Bacon Club Sandwich"

  Ingredients:

  3 slices thin sandwich bread, lightly toasted
  2 tablespoons mayonnaise
  2 slices cooked bacon, halved
  2 tomato slices
  ½ ounce thinly sliced Cheddar cheese
  ⅓ cup sliced cucumber
  ¼ cup shredded carrot
  2 large lettuce leaves

  Directions:
  1. Spread mayonnaise on one side of each toast slice. 
  2. Layer bacon and tomatoes on one slice. 
  3. Top with a second slice, then layer cheese, cucumber, carrot and lettuce. 
  4. Top with the third slice. 
  5. Slice the sandwich on the diagonal.

- "Chicken, Spinach & Feta Wrap"

  Ingredients:
  1/2 cup whole-milk plain strained (Greek-style) yogurt
  1/4 cup crumbled feta cheese
  2 tablespoons finely chopped oil-packed sun-dried tomatoes
  1 tablespoon dried oregano
  2 teaspoons grated lemon zest
  1/2 teaspoon garlic powder
  1/2 teaspoon crushed red pepper
  1/4 teaspoon ground pepper
  2 cups shredded rotisserie chicken
  4 (10-inch) whole wheat tortillas
  4 cups packed fresh baby spinach

  Directions:
  1. Stir together 1 cup yogurt, 1/2 cup feta, sun-dried tomatoes, oregano, lemon zest, garlic powder, crushed red pepper, and pepper.
  2. Fold in chicken.
  3. Place 1 cup spinach and about 1/2 cup chicken mixture in the center of each tortilla.
  4. Fold the bottom edge and side edges over the filling.
  5. Roll up burrito-style.
  6. Cut into halves before serving.

Dinner:
- "Sheet-Pan Salmon with Crispy Quinoa:"

  Ingredients:
  4 (4.4-ounce) packages pre-cooked microwaveable white and red quinoa (such as Minute) (about 2 3/4 cups)
  5 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil, divided
  3 cups cherry tomatoes
  3 tablespoons drained nonpareil capers
  2 tablespoons balsamic vinegar
  1/4 teaspoon ground pepper
  4 (5-ounce) skin-on salmon fillets
  3/4 teaspoon salt, divided
  1/4 cup torn fresh basil leaves
  1/2 teaspoon refrigerated garlic paste
  1/2 teaspoon red wine vinegar

  Directions:
  1. Preheat oven to 425°F and line 2 baking sheets with parchment paper.
  2. Spread quinoa on one sheet, drizzle with 2 tbsp oil, and toss to coat.
  3. On the other sheet, toss tomatoes with capers, balsamic vinegar, pepper, and 2 tbsp oil. 
  4. Arrange salmon fillets in the center, drizzle with 1 tbsp oil, and sprinkle with 1/4 tsp salt.
  5. Place quinoa on the top rack and salmon on the lower rack. Bake for about 15 minutes.
  6. Stir quinoa with a fork and let stand for 5 minutes. Stir in the remaining 1/2 tsp salt.
  7. Divide quinoa and salmon among 4 plates.
  8. Stir basil, garlic paste, and red wine vinegar into the tomato mixture. 
  9. Spoon over salmon before serving.

- "Chickpea Pasta with Mushrooms & Kale:"

  Ingredients:
  8 ounces chickpea rotini or penne
  ¼ cup extra-virgin olive oil
  2 large cloves garlic, sliced
  Pinch of crushed red pepper
  8 cups chopped kale
  8 ounces cremini mushrooms, quartered
  ½ teaspoon dried thyme
  ½ teaspoon salt
  Grated Parmesan cheese for serving

  Directions:
  1. Cook pasta according to package instructions. 2. Reserve 1 cup of cooking water, then drain.
  3. Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat. 
  4. Add garlic and crushed red pepper; cook for about 1 minute until fragrant.
  5. Add kale, mushrooms, thyme, and salt to the skillet. 
  6. Cook for about 5 minutes until vegetables are soft, stirring occasionally.
  7. Stir in cooked pasta and enough reserved water to coat. Cook for about 1 more minute until heated through.
  8. Serve topped with Parmesan, if desired.

- "Chicken Tikka Masala with Rice:"

  Ingredients:
  1½ tablespoons canola oil
  1½ pounds boneless, skinless chicken thighs, cut into 2-inch pieces
  1½ cups chopped yellow onion (from 1 medium onion)
  5 medium garlic cloves, chopped
  1 tablespoon grated fresh ginger
  2 tablespoons canned no-salt-added tomato paste
  1½ teaspoons ground turmeric
  1½ teaspoons garam masala
  ¼ teaspoon cayenne pepper
  1 15-ounce can of no-salt-added tomato puree
  1 cup unsalted chicken stock
  ¼ cup heavy cream
  ¾ teaspoon kosher salt
  ½ teaspoon black pepper
  2 tablespoons chopped fresh cilantro
  2 cups cooked long-grain brown rice

  Directions:
  1. Heat oil in a large, heavy pot over high heat.
  2. Add 1 pound of chicken; cook until browned, about 5 to 6 minutes, turning occasionally.
  3. Add 1 chopped onion, 3 cloves of minced garlic, and a 1-inch piece of grated ginger; cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.
  4. Stir in 2 tablespoons of tomato paste, 1 teaspoon of turmeric, 1 teaspoon of garam masala, and 1/4 teaspoon of cayenne; cook, stirring constantly, for about 2 minutes until spices are toasted and fragrant.
  5. Add 1 cup of tomato puree, 1 cup of chicken stock, 1/2 cup of cream, 1/2 teaspoon of salt, and 1/4 teaspoon of pepper. Bring to a simmer over medium-high heat.
  6. Reduce heat to medium and simmer, stirring occasionally, until sauce is slightly thickened, about 10 minutes.
  7. Stir in a handful of chopped cilantro and serve over rice.

Snacks:
- "Chicken Caesar Salad:"

  Ingredients:
  1 1/2 teaspoons Dijon mustard, divided
  1 teaspoon grated garlic, divided
  1/4 teaspoon ground pepper, divided
  8 ounces chicken tenders
  4 tablespoons extra-virgin olive oil, divided
  1/2 cup whole-milk plain strained (Greek-style) yogurt 
   5 tablespoons grated Parmesan cheese, divided
  1 teaspoon lower-sodium Worcestershire sauce
  1/2 teaspoon anchovy paste
  1/4 teaspoon lemon juice
  4 cups chopped romaine lettuce hearts
  1/2 cup Caesar-seasoned croutons

  Directions:
  1. Combine 1 tsp mustard, 1/2 tsp garlic, and 1/8 tsp pepper in a bowl. Add chicken; coat evenly.
  2. Heat 1 tbsp oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. 
  3. Cook chicken until golden brown and internal temperature reaches 165°F, 6-9 minutes. Let rest for 5 minutes before slicing.
  4. Whisk together yogurt, 3 tbsp Parmesan, Worcestershire sauce, anchovy paste, lemon juice, remaining 1/2 tsp mustard, 1/2 tsp garlic, and 1/8 tsp pepper until creamy.
  5. Add lettuce to the dressing; toss to coat.
  6. Divide dressed lettuce between 2 plates. Top with croutons and sliced chicken. Sprinkle with remaining 2 tbsp Parmesan.

- "Apple & Peanut Butter Toast:"

  Ingredients:
  1 slice whole-grain bread, toasted
  2 tablespoons peanut butter
  ¼ cup sliced apple
  Pinch ground cardamom

  Directions:
  1. Toast bread until golden brown.
  2. Spread peanut butter on each slice.
  3. Top with apple slices.
  4. Sprinkle with cardamom.

  - "Acai Bowl:"

  Ingredients:
  1 banana
  ½ cup frozen mixed berries
  1 (3.5-ounce) package frozen unsweetened acai puree
  ¼ cup fat-free plain strained yogurt, such as Greek-style
  ¼ cup coconut water
  1 tablespoon almond butter
  ⅛ teaspoon ground cinnamon
  2 tablespoons dried goji berries
  2 tablespoons sliced almonds, toasted (see Tip)
  1 teaspoon chia seeds
  1 teaspoon hemp seeds

  Directions:
  1. Cut banana in half crosswise; peel one half and set aside the other.
  2. Place peeled banana half on a parchment-lined freezer-safe plate; freeze for 2 hours.
  3. In a blender, combine frozen banana, berries, acai puree, yogurt, coconut water, almond butter, and cinnamon. Blend until smooth, about 30-45 seconds.
  4. Peel and slice the reserved banana half.
  5. Pour smoothie into a bowl.
  6. Top with banana slices, goji berries, almonds, chia seeds, and hemp seeds.
